            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>March 24 (Reuters) - Wall Street's main indexes opened lower on Tuesday as renewed doubts over easing Middle East tensions tempered the previous session's relief rally despite President Donald Trump's decision to delay strikes on Iran's power grid.</p><p>\n              The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 108.6 points, or 0.24%, at the open to 46,099.86. The S&amp;P 500 fell 28.9 points, or 0.44%, to 6,552.09, while the Nasdaq Composite dropped 139.2 points, or 0.63%, to 21,807.597.</p><!-- Article --><p></p><p> (Reporting by Purvi Agarwal in Bengaluru; Editing by Maju Samuel)</p></div>",
